	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As I understand, most of them simply <em>snap</em> together, and there is a somewhat reliable method for opening them:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">--\*<br />|&nbsp; \l<br />|t |a<br />|o |b<br />|p |e<br />|&nbsp; /l<br />--/*</div>
<br />
<br />1. Hold the cartridge so the label is facing the palm of your hand.
<br />
<br />2. Squeeze the curved edges together (marked *) from the front using your index finger and thumb.
<br />
<br />3. Pull the cartridge apart.
<br />
<br />I don't know if this works on all carts, and I haven't tried it myself, but I have seen the method recommended and it apparently works reasonably well.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


